adjectives.description: foxproof (comparative more foxproof, superlative most foxproof)

entries.meaning: Resistant to the predations of foxes.
examples: We raise our chickens in a foxproof pen.

verbs.description: foxproof (third-person singular simple present foxproofs, present participle foxproofing, simple past and past participle foxproofed)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To make resistant to the predations of foxes.
